.TH "BLUETOOTHCTL-MGMT" "1" "July 2023" "BlueZ" "Linux System Administration"
.SH NAME
bluetoothctl-mgmt \- Management Submenu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBbluetoothctl\fP [\-\-options] [mgmt.commands]
.sp
\fBNOTE:\fP
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
This submenu communicates directly with the kernel via the Bluetooth
Management socket (mgmt), bypassing the BlueZ D\-Bus API. Commands use the
Bluetooth Management API defined in the kernel documentation.
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH MGMT COMMANDS
.SS select
.sp
Select a different index
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B Usage
\fB> select <index>\fP
.TP
.B <index>
Controller index number (0\-based) to select
.TP
.B Example Select controller index 0 (hci0)
.nf
\fB> select 0\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Select controller index 1 (hci1)
.nf
\fB> select 1\fP
.fi
.sp
.TP
.B Example Select controller index 2 (hci2)
.nf
\fB> select 2\fP
.fi
.sp
.UNINDENT
